  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Creating Strong and Self-reliant Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to support farmers of four communities&#x2014;Huay Luk, Pa Bong, Na siri, and Mae Ken&#x2014;who live in remote areas of Chiang Dao district, Chiangmai province. Throughout the five-year project period, 191 original families will receive 100 female buffaloes, four male buffaloes, 455 pigs, four boars, four livestock medical funds and nearly 5 tons of red kidney bean seeds. Another 464 families will benefit from Passing on the Gift. All families participating in the project will receive capacity building through the Values-Based Holistic Community Development approach. The original families in the project will form two self-help groups in each community.  In total, 8 self-help groups will form, two of which will be women-only groups.  To strengthen families, the project will train the self-help groups on development concept, leadership building, basic animal husbandry, animal feed production, integrated agriculture and sustainable natural resource management.</narrative>
  </description>
